The '''RNA brainwashing virus''' was an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] project developed to insert RNA into the brains of [[Sentience/Legends|sentients]]. Because memories were made of RNA, it was thought that this virus would enable the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] to brainwash anyone they wished, which was self-propagating and would destroy any chance of a rebellion. Though the researchers were screened for [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] sympathies, they were so horrified by the implications of the research that they destroyed the project and defected to the Rebel Alliance. A [[Data-tape/Legends|datatape]] containing their research turned up in an auction aboard the ''[[Ananuru Express]]'' and, though [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Imperial Intelligence]] agent [[Secesh Trant]] attempted to steal it, it was recovered by a group of Rebels. It was thought to have then been destroyed so it could never fall into the wrong hands.

